title: US Coast Gaurd and NASA, Schematic of the GOM Oil Slick as of  May 02 2010, World, May 2010
name: US Coast Gaurd and NASA, Schematic of the GOM Oil Slick as of  May 02 2010, World, May 2010
description:
The line shapefile is a schematic of extent of the BP oil slick in the Gulf of Mexico as of May 02, 2010. The US Coast Guard generated the image using the Satellite photo from NASA. The Coast Guard image was geo-referenced and then the outline of the oil-slick was sketched using the drawing toolbox, the line sketch then was converted into a shapefile. 
Look elsewhere on Finder! for oil slick extents as of 26th and 29th Apr, 2010 along with related data of Environmental Sensitivity Index of Louisiana coast line.

author.source: US Coast Guard image gallery website
